# llamabench

Root invariants for the llamabench codebase. Picked up by `find_all_sdd`
and surfaced to the model in the task prompt when `set_repo_root`
points at the llamabench checkout itself; read by humans and Claude Code
as the authoritative architectural contract.

llamabench is a fork of llamabench (`~/Downloads/llamabench`) whose purpose is to run
the same agentic loop against **dense** models instead of the MoE
champion llamabench pinned to. Sourced from `lessons.md` postmortems and the
durable rules carried over from llamabench's auto-memory.

## Must
- Mono-only execution mode (single capable model, full tool surface)
- temp=0.0 in production fixture configs
- All mono prompt edits go through `src/llamabench/agents/prompts.py` registry
- Pin `--work-dir ~/.llamabench/bench-workspace` for bench runs (random tempdir leaks into prompts)
- `oMLX` `idle_timeout_seconds: 1800` (null keeps models resident forever)
- `--keep-loaded` for bench mode (post-run unload fires by default)

## Must not
- Read `origin/<branch>` in offline-cache repos (stale-ref trap; use local ref or sidecar regrade)
- Use any MoE model family — this fork is dense-only by purpose (subsumes llamabench's narrower MoE Instruct-2507 ban)
- Use `--no-verify`, `--no-gpg-sign`, or other hook-skip flags
- Force-push to `main` or `master`
- Configure dense >30B mxfp8 models (granite-4.1-30b-mxfp8 spiked 22GB+ wired and pushed system into swap)
- Write into `~/.llamabench/fixture-cache/` (chmod-locked read-only; llamabench shares the cache as immutable artifact store)

## Owns
- src/llamabench/**

## Forbids
- src/swarm/**
- src/micro/**
- src/phased/**
- src/llamabench/**
